## 2026-02-06: Failed to lint after merging upstream changes

**Context:** After renaming/removing function parameters across multiple files, I merged latest master. The merge completed with no git conflicts.

**Mistake:** I reported the merge as successful without running any lint or type checks. Master had added new test code that called the old interface (with the removed `latestFullEnrichedAt` parameter), which compiled fine before my changes but was now broken. The user had to catch and fix it manually.

**Better approach:** Always run lint checks (`npx biome check` or `ReadLints`) on changed files after a merge/rebase, even if git reports no conflicts. A conflict-free merge does not mean the result is semantically correct — new code from upstream may reference symbols you renamed or removed.

**Lesson:** Treat a merge the same as any other code change: verify correctness with lint/typecheck before reporting success.

