## 2026-03-10: Accidentally deleted an existing comment when refactoring surrounding code

**Context:** Threading a `region` parameter through `handleEnrichment` in `job.ts`. I needed to move the `if (!model)` null check earlier in the function (before a new workspace lookup). The `featureFlagContext` block had a comment explaining why the user context was used.

**Mistake:** When I rewrote the `handleEnrichment` function to reorder the null check and add the workspace lookup, I dropped an existing comment (`// Using the user context so we can keep track of the modelId and workspaceID // in one context (since modelId only lives in the user context).`) from the `featureFlagContext` block. The user had to notice this in the PR diff and restore it manually.

**Better approach:** When rewriting or restructuring a code block, explicitly check that all comments from the original are preserved in the new version. Comments are invisible to linters and type checkers, so they're the easiest thing to accidentally drop.

**Lesson:** After rewriting a block of code, scan the original for comments and verify each one is present in the new version.

