## 2026-03-19: `gh pr edit` fails silently due to GraphQL deprecation warning

**Context:** After creating PR #34059, user asked to make the description more concise. I used `gh pr edit 34059 --body "..."` and `gh pr edit 34059 --body-file /tmp/body.md` — both returned exit code 1 with a GraphQL deprecation warning about "Projects (classic)" but no other error. I assumed it failed and retried multiple times before discovering the body was never updated.

**Mistake:** `gh pr edit` uses the GraphQL API internally. The "Projects (classic)" deprecation warning causes exit code 1, and the edit is silently **not applied**. I wasted 3 round trips trying different variations of the same broken command before switching to the REST API.

**Definitive `gh` commands for PR operations:**

| Operation | Command | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| **Create PR** | `gh pr create --title "..." --body "$(cat <<'EOF' ... EOF)"` | Works reliably |
| **Update PR body** | `gh api repos/OWNER/REPO/pulls/NUM -X PATCH -F body=@file` | REST API — always use this, not `gh pr edit` |
| **Update PR title** | `gh api repos/OWNER/REPO/pulls/NUM -X PATCH -f title="new title"` | REST API |
| **View PR** | `gh pr view NUM --json body,title,state` | Works reliably |
| **Get PR comments** | `gh api repos/OWNER/REPO/pulls/NUM/comments` | REST API |
| **Get review comments** | `gh api repos/OWNER/REPO/pulls/NUM/reviews` | REST API |
| **Add reviewers** | `gh pr edit NUM --add-reviewer user1,user2` | May hit same GraphQL bug — use REST if it fails |
| **Check CI** | `gh pr checks NUM` | Works reliably |

**Key rule:** Never use `gh pr edit --body` or `--body-file`. Always use `gh api ... -X PATCH -F body=@file` for updating PR bodies. Write the body to a temp file first, then pass it with `-F body=@/tmp/file.md`.

**Lesson:** When a `gh` subcommand returns exit code 1 with only a deprecation warning and no visible error, assume the operation silently failed. Fall back to the REST API (`gh api`).

